cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper presents a new variant of the Twin Support Vector Machine (TWSVM) to deal with large datasets and learning from data streams. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a dual coordinate descent algorithm with a shrinking strategy, which is commonly used in optimization problems (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper proposes an extension of the FBTWSVM for multi-class problems, which falls under the category of neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE) and signal processing (cs.SI).
